COMPONENT NAME: LKM Oracle to Oracle (datapump)
AUTHOR: Oracle
DESCRIPTION - Loads data from an Oracle Server to an Oracle Server using external tables in the datapump format. - This module is recommended when developing interfaces between two Oracle servers when DBLINK is not an option. - An External table definition is created on the source and target servers. - When using this module on a journalized source table, the Journaling table is first updated to flag the records consumed and then cleaned from these records at the end of the interface. - Data can be loaded in parallel by using the option PARALLEL_LOADS
OPTIONS - COMPATIBLE: Version of objects to export where valid keywords are: (COMPATIBLE), LATEST, or any valid database version. If this parameter is not populated, COMPATIBLE is the default operating mode. - TEMP_DIR: Temporary directory where the data is written to - DELETE_TEMPORARY_OBJECTS: Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging. - PARALLEL_LOADS: Number of worker processes to be employed to load data in parallel
LIMITATIONS - Both RDBMS instances must live on same physical server. The datapump export file cannot be written to a shared directory. - When exporting from a higher RDBMS version to a lower version, the COMPATIBLE parameter must be used to match the target RDBMS version.

Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging. NB : Database links are managed by the AUTO_CREATE_DB_LINK option in order to avoid an unexpected deletion
